To solve \(8464_9 + 61527_9\), we will convert both numbers from base-9 to base-10, perform the addition in base-10, and then convert the result back to base-9.

First, convert \(8464_9\) to base-10:

\[ 8464_9 = 8 \cdot 9^3 + 4 \cdot 9^2 + 6 \cdot 9^1 + 4 \cdot 9^0 \]

Calculate each term:

\[ 8 \cdot 9^3 = 8 \cdot 729 = 5832 \]
\[ 4 \cdot 9^2 = 4 \cdot 81 = 324 \]
\[ 6 \cdot 9^1 = 6 \cdot 9 = 54 \]
\[ 4 \cdot 9^0 = 4 \cdot 1 = 4 \]

Sum these results to get the base-10 equivalent:

\[ 8464_9 = 5832 + 324 + 54 + 4 = 6214_{10} \]

Next, convert \(61527_9\) to base-10:

\[ 61527_9 = 6 \cdot 9^4 + 1 \cdot 9^3 + 5 \cdot 9^2 + 2 \cdot 9^1 + 7 \cdot 9^0 \]

Calculate each term:

\[ 6 \cdot 9^4 = 6 \cdot 6561 = 39366 \]
\[ 1 \cdot 9^3 = 1 \cdot 729 = 729 \]
\[ 5 \cdot 9^2 = 5 \cdot 81 = 405 \]
\[ 2 \cdot 9^1 = 2 \cdot 9 = 18 \]
\[ 7 \cdot 9^0 = 7 \cdot 1 = 7 \]

Sum these results to get the base-10 equivalent:

\[ 61527_9 = 39366 + 729 + 405 + 18 + 7 = 40525_{10} \]

Now, add the two base-10 numbers:

\[ 6214 + 40525 = 46739_{10} \]

Finally, convert \(46739_{10}\) back to base-9. We'll repeatedly divide by 9 and keep track of the remainders:

\[ 46739 \div 9 = 5193 \quad \text{remainder} \ 2 \]
\[ 5193 \div 9 = 577 \quad \text{remainder} \ 0 \]
\[ 577 \div 9 = 64 \quad \text{remainder} \ 1 \]
\[ 64 \div 9 = 7 \quad \text{remainder} \ 1 \]
\[ 7 \div 9 = 0 \quad \text{remainder} \ 7 \]

Reading the remainders from last to first, we get:

\[ 46739_{10} = 71102_{9} \]

Thus, the result of the equation is:

\[ 8464_{9} + 61527_{9} = 46739_{10} = 71102_{9} \]

Summary in the required format:

\[ 8464_9 + 61527_9 = 6214_{10} + 40525_{10} = 46739_{10} = 71102_9 \]